Net-MyCommerce-API

This module provides sample code to access the Digital River MyCommerce Platform REST API.

More information about these APIs are available at url:
http://help.mycommerce.com/index.php/mycommerce-apis

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

  perl Makefile.PL
  make
  make test
  make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

  Encode
  JSON::Parse
  JSON::XS
  MIME::Base64
  REST::Client
  Try::Tiny
  URI::Escape

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

  perldoc Net::MyCommerce::API

Online documentation for the Digital River MyCommerce APIs is available at
  
  http://help.mycommerce.com/index.php/mycommerce-apis

You can also look for information at:

  RT, CPAN's request tracker
    http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Net-MyCommerce-API

  AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
    http://annocpan.org/dist/Net-MyCommerce-API

  CPAN Ratings
    http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Net-MyCommerce-API

  Search CPAN
    http://search.cpan.org/dist/Net-MyCommerce-API/

EXAMPLES

/examples subdirectory include a few sample scripts.
You will need to have a MyCommerce vendor ID and appropriately scoped API secrets.
Also some scripts require one or two product IDs.

